          <div class="spec-row"><span>Setting</span><span>Tarrytown</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="agent" class="agent">
  <div class="agent-photo">
    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1573497019940-1c28c88b4f3e?auto=format&fit=crop&w=900&q=85" alt="Sarah Chen">
  </div>
  <div class="agent-copy">
    <div class="agent-label">The Agent</div>
    <h2 class="agent-h2">Quietly relentless.<br><i>Exceptionally precise.</i></h2>
    <p class="agent-bio">Sarah Chen entered Austin real estate in 2013 with a background in architecture and a conviction that most agents were solving the wrong problem. Her clients don't need someone to open doors. They need someone who has already read every disclosure, walked every comparable, and knows which three streets in Tarrytown will appreciate fastest over the next decade.</p>
    <p class="agent-bio">She handles a maximum of twelve transactions per year. By choice.</p>
    <div class="agent-creds">
      <span class="cred">Top 1% Austin Board of Realtors, 2019–2024</span>
      <span class="cred">Certified Luxury Home Marketing Specialist</span>
      <span class="cred">Architecture, UT Austin B.Arch 2008</span>
      <span class="cred">Fluent in Mandarin and Spanish</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="testimonial">
  <div class="t-meta">
    <span class="t-label">Client Review</span>
    <div class="t-year">2023</div>
  </div>
  <div>
    <p class="t-quote">"Sarah found us a home we didn't know existed. Three weeks after our first call, we were under contract on a property that had never officially hit the market. That's not luck. That's access."</p>
    <div class="t-author">Marcus & Elena Whitfield · Westlake Hills</div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="contact" class="contact">
  <div class="contact-left">
